-- 
Romania to Cut 1,300 Jobs in Energy Companies to Meet IMF Pledge

-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 
2011-07-27T11:36:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/romania-to-cut-1-300-jobs-in-energy-companies-to-meet-imf-pledge.html
Romania  will cut 1,300 jobs at three
state-owned energy companies this year as it seeks to meet its
pledges to the  International Monetary Fund  and the European
Union.  Nine hundred people will be fired from Compania Nationala a
Huilei Petrosani, a miner in southern Romania, 300 people will
be dismissed from SC Termocentrale Bucuresti and 100 employees
will have to leave SC Electrocentrale Deva, the Bucharest-based
government said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez in Prague at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  